cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and emotion detection in social media posts. It may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it explores the dependence among relevant posts via the authors' backgrounds. Additionally, it involves the use of neural networks, which makes it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of attention mechanisms, which is relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with personal attributes, which may make it relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
